<h2 class="heading2">Modifying Slots</h2>
<p class="bodytext">To modify a Slot:</p>
<ol class="listnumber"><li class="listnumber">In Assembly Design view, double-click on the Slot you want to edit.<p class="listcontinue">The Workbench displays the <a id="h13116" class="jumptemplate" title="Slot Editor" href="13114.htm" target="_self">Slot editor</a>.</p>
</li><li class="listnumber">You can change the value in the <strong class="specialbold">Label</strong> or <strong class="specialbold">Description</strong> field.</li><li class="listnumber">To add a Content Type and Template (or Variant) to the Slot:<ol class="listalpha2"><li class="listalpha2">In the first blank row of the <strong class="specialbold">Content Type</strong> column, click the drop arrow and choose the Content Type you want to assign to the Slot.  Options include all Content Types not currently assigned to the Slot.</li><li class="listalpha2">In the corresponding row of the <strong class="specialbold">Template</strong> column, click the drop arrow and choose the Template you want to use to format Content Items of the specified Content Type.  Options include all Templates available for that Content Type.  (NOTE:  If you did not specify a Content Finder, the heading on this column is <strong class="specialbold">Variants</strong> and the options include all Variants associated with the Content Type.)</li></ol></li><li class="listnumber">To remove a Content Type and its associated Template from the Slot, select the Content Type you want to delete and press the &lt;Delete&gt; key on your keyboard.</li><li class="listnumber">To change the <strong class="specialbold">Content Finder</strong>,:<ol class="listalpha2"><li class="listalpha2">Choose another option from the drop list.  </li><li class="listalpha2">Click the browse button <img src="browsebtn.gif" alt="Browse Button" height="100" width="100" vspace="2" hspace="2" align="bottom" border="0">  next to the Content finder field to display the Extensions editor.</li><li class="listalpha2">Specify values for the Content Finder parameters.  </li><li class="listalpha2">Click the [<strong class="buttons">OK</strong>] button to close the Extensions editor.</li></ol></li><li class="listnumber">Changing the value in the <strong class="specialbold">Type</strong> or <strong class="specialbold">Allowed Relationship Type</strong> field is not recommended.</li><li class="listnumber">Click the [<strong class="buttons">Save</strong>] button to save your changes.</li></ol><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0">
